	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Nairobi - Kenyan opposition leader Raila Odinga had himself sworn in as an alternative president Tuesday in front of thousands of supporters, three months after claiming an election was stolen from him. "I Raila Amolo Odinga, in full realisation of the high calling, assume the office of the People's President of the Republic of Kenya," he said in the brief and chaotic ceremony surrounded by a sea of people in Nairobi. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  